<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-31T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-31T03:00:00-05:00" n="768" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2798: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-31T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 31,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 7:32
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>432. Your 253, October 27, 4 p.m. Note delivered to Foreign Office today.
                            British, French and Japanese Legations also delivered notes of similar
                            purport. Italian Legation will join in representations as soon as
                            instructions are received from Rome.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>